"'''Hero of Cartao'''" was a serialized short story written by [[Timothy Zahn]] and illustrated by [[Douglas Chaffee]] that appeared in ''[[Star Wars Insider]]'' magazine. It was separated into three parts: "'''Hero's Call'''" (Issue 68), "'''Hero's Rise'''" (Issue 69), and "'''Hero's End'''" (Issue 70). It featured such characters as [[Jafer Torles]] and the pre-existing Zahn character of [[Kinman Doriana/Legends|Kinman Doriana]]. It took place in [[22 BBY/Legends|22 BBY]]<ref name="ERC" /><ref name="Heroes on Both Sides" /> and was essentially the story of how the [[Spaarti cloning cylinder]]s came to [[Wayland/Legends|Wayland]].

==Plot summary==
{{Plot|story}}

==Release and reception==
It was printed in ''[[Star Wars: The Official Magazine 67]]'' under the misspelled title of "'''Hero of Cartoa'''."

